Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at a retreat for American business leaders, thanking them for their support and highlighting President Donald Trump's commitment to the American people. Pence praised Trump's actions to cut regulations and unleash American energy, stating that the era of over-regulation is over and the war on coal is over. He also discussed the administration's efforts to repeal and replace Obamacare, including an executive order to expand access to association health plans. Pence emphasized the importance of tax cuts, outlining the four principles of the administration's tax-cut plan: giving working families a historic tax cut, simplifying the tax code, making American business competitive again, and cutting taxes on overseas earnings. He urged business leaders to support the plan and communicate its importance to their employees, suppliers, and elected officials. Pence concluded by expressing confidence in the American people and their ability to build a prosperous future for the nation.